

---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Article from "../../components/Article.astro";
---

<Layout title="intuition">
  <Article
    title="intuition"
    section="self"
    updated="archive draft"
  >
    <p>
      intuition is a form of knowing that does not move step by step. it appears
      as a sense, a direction, or a pattern recognized without deliberate
      reasoning.
    </p>

    <p>
      it often arrives quickly, before language fully forms. what is known is
      felt first, then explained later.
    </p>

    <p>
      because of this, intuition can feel immediate and certain—but it is not
      always correct.
    </p>

    <h2>pattern recognition</h2>

    <p>
      intuition draws on accumulated experience, even when that experience is
      not consciously recalled. patterns are recognized beneath awareness.
    </p>

    <p>
      this allows for rapid understanding, but makes the source of the knowledge
      difficult to trace.
    </p>

    <h2>speed</h2>

    <p>
      intuitive knowing is fast. it does not unfold through analysis, but
      presents itself as a whole.
    </p>

    <p>
      this speed can be useful, but it can also lead to error if not examined.
    </p>

    <h2>discernment</h2>

    <p>
      not every intuitive impression is accurate. distinguishing between
      intuition, impulse, and projection requires attention.
    </p>

    <p>
      over time, discernment develops by testing what is felt against what
      unfolds in reality.
    </p>

    <div class="mini-links">
      <a class="link-blue" href="/self">back to self index</a>
      <a class="link-blue" href="/self/play">continue to: play</a>
      <a class="link-red" href="/self/identity">identity</a>
    </div>
  </Article>
</Layout>